-What are you talking about?

00:41:41.041 --> 00:41:43.583
- My interest in History.

00:41:44.583 --> 00:41:47.125
Anyway, I’ll see you later.

00:41:47.333 --> 00:41:47.708
-Okay.

00:41:47.708 --> 00:41:48.166
-Yes.

00:41:50.625 --> 00:41:51.958
Sit , sit, sit…..

00:41:52.875 --> 00:41:55.666
I think I’ve figured out
what “5-8-75” means.

00:41:57.000 --> 00:41:58.958
“5-8-75, Hasting’s revenge”?

00:42:00.625 --> 00:42:02.250
I’ve made a huge
mistake by calling you here.

00:42:02.375 --> 00:42:02.708
-Why ?

00:42:02.916 --> 00:42:03.750
Now, you’re going to bore me

00:42:03.750 --> 00:42:04.791
With details about Hastings.

00:42:04.875 --> 00:42:05.500
Just hear me out.

00:42:05.500 --> 00:42:05.875
Don’t worry about it.

00:42:06.000 --> 00:42:06.791
It’s very interesting.

00:42:07.041 --> 00:42:07.625
Let me tell you the story.

00:42:08.458 --> 00:42:11.250
After Mirjafar died,
Diwan Nandakumar…

00:42:11.708 --> 00:42:15.375
…reported against Warren Hastings
corruption to the East India Company.

00:42:16.083 --> 00:42:19.375
And as payback,
Hastings filed a case against Nandakumar…

00:42:20.125 --> 00:42:22.541
…claiming he forged documents.

00:42:22.875 --> 00:42:25.166
Nandakumar has
sentenced to be hanged.

00:42:25.666 --> 00:42:28.250
The date of the
hanging was ‘5-8-1775”.

00:42:29.416 --> 00:42:31.958
This riddle talks
about Nandakumar.

00:42:32.958 --> 00:42:35.541
What does that have
to do with my mom ?

00:42:36.125 --> 00:42:37.166
They are related in some way.

00:42:38.791 --> 00:42:40.041
We need to find out how.

00:42:42.458 --> 00:42:44.000
Hey, I think my brother’s here.

00:42:57.666 --> 00:42:58.166
-Brother…

00:42:58.458 --> 00:43:00.041
-Tell me. -Why are you so late ?

00:43:00.166 --> 00:43:01.458
-Just… Your flight was delayed?

00:43:01.791 --> 00:43:02.500
-By two hours.

00:43:03.541 --> 00:43:04.250
This came for you.

00:43:04.875 --> 00:43:05.583
What’s this ?

00:43:08.958 --> 00:43:09.625
I didn’t open it.

00:43:10.041 --> 00:43:10.500
It was Dad.

00:43:13.041 --> 00:43:15.291
I have no privacy in this house.

00:43:16.833 --> 00:43:20.250
The bank’s recovery agents
have already come home twice.

00:43:20.458 --> 00:43:21.791
Dad is trying hard
to keep them at bay.

00:43:21.916 --> 00:43:23.041
Thank him for his favour.

00:43:25.458 --> 00:43:26.375
Can i tell you something?

00:43:27.208 --> 00:43:28.708
Please stop spending
money excessively.

00:43:30.333 --> 00:43:31.416
What are you talking about?

00:43:32.166 --> 00:43:33.666
You buy a phone every month…

00:43:34.375 --> 00:43:36.791
You buy a new car often…

00:43:36.875 --> 00:43:38.708
You’re throwing
extravagant parties…

00:43:38.958 --> 00:43:41.083
Travelling abroad… Don’t you
think you’re spending too much?

00:43:42.125 --> 00:43:43.625
You might not understand it.

00:43:44.791 --> 00:43:46.291
But these are
necessities for me.

00:43:53.625 --> 00:43:54.583
That’s enough for me.

00:43:57.625 --> 00:43:59.125
So, researching History, I see…

00:44:00.708 --> 00:44:02.833
That’s great but
what’s the point?

00:44:04.791 --> 00:44:06.708
You’ll ultimately
become a professor.

00:44:07.083 --> 00:44:09.291
So,
what’s wrong with being a professor?

00:44:13.583 --> 00:44:17.000
Where do you live ?
What does your father do ?

00:44:21.625 --> 00:44:23.125
Soham has grown
up in an orphanage.

00:44:23.875 --> 00:44:25.000
He doesn’t know
who his parents are.

00:44:26.625 --> 00:44:28.125
Dad and I don’t
have a problem with it.

00:44:28.750 --> 00:44:31.291
Right, Dad?

00:44:36.333 --> 00:44:37.833
Can you pass me the gravy?

00:44:44.666 --> 00:44:46.166
Sir.

00:45:41.833 --> 00:45:42.916
-Hey! Hey! Hey!

00:45:42.916 --> 00:45:43.375
-What happened?

00:45:44.000 --> 00:45:45.708
Why are you
littering this place?

00:45:46.916 --> 00:45:48.416
Get out of here.

00:45:49.791 --> 00:45:51.083
-Hello, Nitai.

00:45:51.291 --> 00:45:52.333
-Hello, sir.

00:45:52.500 --> 00:45:53.708
Are you here for the clay?

00:45:54.416 --> 00:45:57.166
Isn’t this clay full of goodness,
Nitai?

00:45:58.416 --> 00:46:01.375
And Mother will come alive.

00:46:03.166 --> 00:46:06.208
She’ll get dressed
at Jorashankho.

00:46:07.291 --> 00:46:09.500
She’ll have a
feast in Kumurtuli…

00:46:10.125 --> 00:46:14.041
She’ll join in the night long
festivities at the Sovabazar Rajbari

00:46:14.458 --> 00:46:17.500
And in the end she’ll come back to the
Ganges and once again become clay.

00:46:18.166 --> 00:46:21.375
To fathom her… Hey!

00:46:22.250 --> 00:46:28.875
You’re not going to stop unless You
turn this place into a junkyard. Right?

00:46:29.750 --> 00:46:30.916
-Get out of here!

00:46:30.916 --> 00:46:33.125
-Sir! What a rascal!

00:46:35.708 --> 00:46:41.083
Who were you talking about?

00:46:41.750 --> 00:46:43.625
Everybody’s Mother.

00:46:44.166 --> 00:46:45.541
Goddess Durga.

00:46:46.166 --> 00:46:48.416
It seems you’ve
forgotten everything.

00:46:48.708 --> 00:46:52.708
How much longer are you going to
tell these stories to be in business?

00:46:53.500 --> 00:46:55.041
Everything is fake
and made up to you.

00:46:56.166 --> 00:46:58.291
My grandfather’s grandfather…

00:46:59.166 --> 00:47:01.333
To make it simple for you…

00:47:01.666 --> 00:47:06.625
My father’s father’s
father’s father…

00:47:07.458 --> 00:47:12.041
…was the priest in Kumurtuli’s
Abhay Charan Mitra’s house.

00:47:12.458 --> 00:47:21.291
If I tell you how much rice was used
in the offering, you’ll go into shock.

00:47:22.000 --> 00:47:25.416
So, the Mother Goddess ate at
Kumurtuli’s Abhay Charan Mitra’s home…

00:47:25.416 --> 00:47:26.708
And where did she dressed up ?

00:47:26.958 --> 00:47:29.833
These are adages from old Kolkata,
son.

00:47:30.541 --> 00:47:35.958
She would wear her jewellery at
Jorashanko’s Shibkrishna Dan’s house.

00:47:37.416 --> 00:47:41.833
She eats at Kumurtuli’s
Abhay Charan Mitra’s home.

00:47:42.833 --> 00:47:47.625
And she attends the festivities
at Sovabazar’s Rajbari.

00:47:48.166 --> 00:47:50.041
Your generation doesn’t
know these things.

00:47:50.750 --> 00:47:52.583
And even if you did
you don’t believe in it.

00:47:53.208 --> 00:47:54.291
I do, sir

00:47:55.625 --> 00:47:56.833
Bless me, sir.

00:48:00.625 --> 00:48:03.916
Only Goddess Durga knows,
If I believed me.

00:48:04.083 --> 00:48:04.833
-Mr. Storyteller!

00:48:05.041 --> 00:48:07.833
-Hey! Will you please leave?

00:48:08.208 --> 00:48:09.708
-This old man is killing me!

00:48:09.708 --> 00:48:10.666
-Disgusting!

00:48:14.958 --> 00:48:17.125
Do you know where
Shibkrishna Dan’s house is?

00:48:17.250 --> 00:48:17.833
-Yes.

00:48:17.833 --> 00:48:18.416
-Okay.

00:48:19.125 --> 00:48:21.500
-We want to go there exactly.
-Got it.

00:48:22.500 --> 00:48:24.458
Who is Shibkrishna Dan ?

00:48:24.666 --> 00:48:26.083
Why are we going to his place ?

00:48:26.500 --> 00:48:28.166
Because Asutosh’s
wife gets dressed there.

00:48:28.708 --> 00:48:32.083
What? Why are you
using my dad’s name?

00:48:32.333 --> 00:48:33.750
I’m not taking about your dad.

00:48:34.333 --> 00:48:35.791
Asutosh is Lord
Shiva’s other name.

00:48:36.500 --> 00:48:39.083
Lord Shiva’s other
name was Somenath too.

00:48:40.166 --> 00:48:42.583
-And what’s Shiva’s wife’s name ?
-Durga. Correct.

00:48:48.666 --> 00:48:50.041
Where the wife dresses up…

00:48:50.833 --> 00:48:52.500
Somnath was
referring to this house.

00:48:53.166 --> 00:48:54.958
According to the adages…

00:48:55.416 --> 00:48:57.916
Goddes Durga wears her jewellery in
Jorashanko’s Shibkrishna Dan’s House.

00:48:59.375 --> 00:49:00.250
-Excellent! Let’s go.

00:49:00.250 --> 00:49:00.875
-Where are you going?

00:49:01.333 --> 00:49:02.416
Ain’t we going in?

00:49:03.000 --> 00:49:04.208
What does the riddle say?

00:49:04.750 --> 00:49:06.875
The lane where the
wide wears her clothes…

00:49:07.166 --> 00:49:08.916
How many does Hutum Byancha’s
collection of ponytails expose?

00:49:09.166 --> 00:49:10.333
-Remember the
number of ponytails?

00:49:10.750 --> 00:49:12.916
-51. Then what can we deduce?

00:49:15.041 --> 00:49:16.750
Absolutely nothing!

00:49:18.375 --> 00:49:22.750
Please pray to Goddess
Durga for some brains.

00:49:23.208 --> 00:49:25.500
What are you trying to say ?

00:49:30.166 --> 00:49:33.375
Do you think I am not smart?

00:49:34.208 --> 00:49:36.125
You’re losing your mind.

00:49:37.875 --> 00:49:40.666
Hey, 51 ponytails mean…

00:49:41.166 --> 00:49:42.583
…we’ve to look for
house number 51?

00:49:43.500 --> 00:49:47.750
You just prayed once and she
has already sent you some brains.

00:49:48.250 --> 00:49:48.708
Shut up!

00:49:50.708 --> 00:49:53.791
How many does Hutum Byancha’s
collection of ponytails expose?

00:49:54.750 --> 00:49:59.250
If you are looking carefully,
you’ll arrive Hastings’ revenge on 5-8-75

00:50:01.250 --> 00:50:04.750
-Sir,
do you know if Nandakumar lives here?

00:50:05.000 --> 00:50:06.458
-Nandakumar Ghosh?
-Yes, This house?

00:50:06.583 --> 00:50:08.041
-Yeah, he lives in this house.

00:50:08.291 --> 00:50:09.958
Let’s go in. Come quickly…

00:50:50.583 --> 00:50:52.833
How are you related to Somnath ?

00:50:53.791 --> 00:50:54.958
I’m not related.

00:50:55.750 --> 00:50:58.500
This is my friend, Brishti.

00:50:59.166 --> 00:51:01.250
Do you know Asutosh Singho?

00:51:02.666 --> 00:51:05.291
Asutosh from the Singho house?

00:51:05.583 --> 00:51:06.041
Yes

00:51:06.291 --> 00:51:07.625
Brishti is his daughter.

00:51:07.875 --> 00:51:10.000
Asutosh and
Somnath were friends.

00:51:11.000 --> 00:51:12.333
He has passed away
a long time back.

00:51:12.625 --> 00:51:13.458
Who?

00:51:15.166 --> 00:51:16.250
-Somnath?

00:51:16.250 --> 00:51:16.833
-Yes.

00:51:20.166 --> 00:51:26.375
Somnath… …has passed away?

00:51:27.250 --> 00:51:28.750
Yes,he passed away.

00:51:30.000 --> 00:51:33.833
And before he passed away,
he sent Asutosh a letter.

00:51:34.833 --> 00:51:36.208
That’s where the riddle was.

00:51:37.083 --> 00:51:41.000
The solution to the riddle will lead
to an object of great historical value.

00:51:41.958 --> 00:51:45.916
So far, it has led us to you.

00:51:47.958 --> 00:51:50.625
Somnath was a curious guy.

00:51:52.416 --> 00:51:58.333
I’ve had many students
but no one like Somnath.

00:52:00.750 --> 00:52:02.416
He respected me a lot.

00:52:04.125 --> 00:52:08.333
I felt… How long it has been?

00:52:09.125 --> 00:52:11.791
-Must be 25 years.. 27 years…

00:52:12.000 --> 00:52:13.750
-27 years…

00:52:15.833 --> 00:52:20.791
Somnath had sent me a
letter before he passed away.

00:52:21.958 --> 00:52:25.625
If anyone came to
me with that riddle..

00:52:26.958 --> 00:52:29.291
I was supposed
to hand this over.

00:52:31.666 --> 00:52:34.125
I’ve been waiting for too long.

00:52:37.625 --> 00:52:39.333
But no one came.

00:52:39.500 --> 00:52:41.750
I have lost my vision too.

00:52:42.958 --> 00:52:44.833
And you ‘ve finally come.

00:52:48.958 --> 00:52:50.958
Take it.

00:52:57.625 --> 00:52:59.750
I am free of my responsibility.

00:53:02.416 --> 00:53:05.583
Didn’t Somnath tell
you anything else?

00:53:06.333 --> 00:53:09.000
No… Nothing else…

00:53:10.083 --> 00:53:13.458
“The sky blue glass in English
puts the Englishman in jail”

00:53:14.625 --> 00:53:18.541
“The birthday of the best translator
will take you home without fail”

00:53:19.833 --> 00:53:20.750
Nine.

00:53:24.125 --> 00:53:25.875
The sky blue glass in English?

00:53:29.916 --> 00:53:32.750
Can you please stop
with the history already?

00:53:33.208 --> 00:53:33.750
Why?

00:53:34.958 --> 00:53:37.333
Because I can’t spend the rest
of my life with a crazy person.

00:53:38.500 --> 00:53:40.666
Somnath Das went
crazy because of History.

00:53:41.291 --> 00:53:45.083
And I think people who study
History also go mad like Somnath Das.

00:53:45.458 --> 00:53:46.791
-May Goddess Durga
give you some brains.

00:53:46.791 --> 00:53:47.250
-Shut up.

00:53:48.083 --> 00:53:50.500
Somnath Das is a crazy guy.

00:53:50.625 --> 00:53:51.833
And I’m sure he’s alive.

00:53:52.291 --> 00:53:58.541
He is secretly sending Dad those notes. And he’s
having a good laugh at our expense, Rubbish!

00:54:00.833 --> 00:54:02.625
-Let’s go. We’ll be late.

00:54:02.750 --> 00:54:03.375
-Where do we have to go ?

00:54:04.083 --> 00:54:06.958
You forgot we’ve to
go to Ranjana’s party?

00:54:07.083 --> 00:54:09.000
Please don’t take me there.

00:54:09.125 --> 00:54:10.291
I feel very uncomfortable.

00:54:10.625 --> 00:54:11.958
-Stop your nonsense. Let’s go.
-Please…

00:54:12.375 --> 00:54:13.791
There’ll be a lot
of traffic in Behala.

00:54:13.833 --> 00:54:17.208
We’ll take James
Long Sarani. Come on.

00:54:17.791 --> 00:54:19.000
James… Hey, Brishti…

00:54:19.333 --> 00:54:22.041
-Can you drop me
off at the library?

00:54:22.166 --> 00:54:23.666
-Am I your driver?

00:54:43.791 --> 00:54:45.958
What’s the first thing that comes to
your mind when you hear the word sky?

00:54:47.458 --> 00:54:48.583
Here we go again.

00:54:49.208 --> 00:54:49.958
Tell me.

00:54:51.083 --> 00:54:52.583
-Sky blue, Indigo…

00:54:52.958 --> 00:54:54.125
-Indigo…

00:54:54.583 --> 00:54:56.166
Now,
give me another word for glass.

00:54:56.708 --> 00:54:57.458
-Mirror…

00:54:57.791 --> 00:54:58.500
-Great!

00:54:59.125 --> 00:55:00.333
That makes it “Nil Darpan” Which
is also called “The Indigo Mirror”.

00:55:00.958 --> 00:55:03.125
Yes, that’s a famous play
ny Dinabandhu Mitra. So?

00:55:03.708 --> 00:55:06.166
The British had
banned this play.

00:55:06.791 --> 00:55:09.583
But an Englishman… Take
the James Long Sarani.

00:55:10.166 --> 00:55:10.708
-Okay, sir.
-What were you saying?

00:55:10.708 --> 00:55:15.333
An Englishman secretly got it translated and sent
it to England. He was sent to prison for this.

00:55:15.791 --> 00:55:20.916
“The sky blue glass in English
puts the Englishman in jail

00:55:21.916 --> 00:55:22.541
Who was he ?

00:55:23.583 --> 00:55:24.833
Reverend James Long.

00:55:25.416 --> 00:55:28.791
-Are we on James Long Sarani.
-Yes, sir.

00:55:30.416 --> 00:55:33.625
“The birthday of the best translator will take
you home without fail” What does this mean?

00:55:34.875 --> 00:55:40.041
It is said that Michael Madhusudan Dutt
translated the play in English overnight.

00:55:40.666 --> 00:55:44.291
And his date of
birth is 25-1-1824.

00:55:44.833 --> 00:55:47.916
25 by 1… Stop the car!

00:55:48.541 --> 00:55:49.500
What happened?

00:55:54.375 --> 00:55:56.000
Where are you going?

00:55:58.333 --> 00:56:02.458
25/1… 25/1… Brishti…

00:56:03.750 --> 00:56:06.208
Dinabandhu Sweet Shop!

00:56:14.125 --> 00:56:16.333
-Somnath Das… My dad talked about him.
-Somnath Das…

00:56:16.916 --> 00:56:17.958
But that’s a long time ago.

00:56:18.291 --> 00:56:19.708
-Can we meet your father?

00:56:20.083 --> 00:56:20.541
-Yes.

00:56:21.916 --> 00:56:23.166
We’re Sorry.

00:56:23.458 --> 00:56:26.750
He used to say Somnath
Das was a chatterbox.

00:56:27.125 --> 00:56:30.750
What was the guy’s name?
Michael Mitra… Dinabandhu Dutt.

00:56:30.916 --> 00:56:34.083
James Long Sarani…
Michael… Please continue…

00:56:34.250 --> 00:56:36.458
There’s some kind of
connection with our shop.

00:56:37.041 --> 00:56:38.541
That’s why he came
to meet my dad.

00:56:38.958 --> 00:56:41.250
He had all the
information about Kolkata.

00:56:41.416 --> 00:56:43.583
My dad also indulged him.

00:56:44.208 --> 00:56:46.666
They were like
two peas in a pod.

00:56:46.666 --> 00:56:47.125
Okay.

00:56:47.291 --> 00:56:48.791
Where are you going?

00:56:49.208 --> 00:56:49.833
Wait one minute.

00:56:50.333 --> 00:56:52.166
Hey, bring a ledikeni sweet.

00:56:52.541 --> 00:56:53.666
-We don’t want
to eat your sweets.

00:56:54.208 --> 00:56:55.791
-I’m not offering either.

00:57:04.875 --> 00:57:06.416
Drop the sweet.

00:57:17.708 --> 00:57:18.958
Dad, I kept my word.

00:57:19.750 --> 00:57:20.791
What is all this ?

00:57:21.500 --> 00:57:22.750
That I don’t know.

00:57:23.083 --> 00:57:25.750
Somnath had sent
a letter to my dad.

00:57:26.333 --> 00:57:29.041
Before he died,
He passed the instruction to me.

00:57:30.250 --> 00:57:31.000
It says…

00:57:31.875 --> 00:57:36.375
“What made this sweet’s father famous,
Seven of those must be put beside it.”

00:57:37.458 --> 00:57:40.000
Who is ledikeni sweet’s father ?

00:57:40.375 --> 00:57:42.250
It can be any of the sweets…

00:57:42.541 --> 00:57:45.500
You can dig deeper into the mystery
of sweets but please pay me Rs. 10.

00:57:52.250 --> 00:57:56.416
Amirchand,I’ll not get any
part of my father’s property.

00:57:57.250 --> 00:57:59.291
Brishti will inherit everything.

00:58:01.375 --> 00:58:05.250
In this situation,
if I can’t get the money,

00:58:05.625 --> 00:58:06.458
I’ll lose the shop.

00:58:07.666 --> 00:58:10.041
I can’t get a loan
from anywhere.

00:58:10.041 --> 00:58:16.750
Abhiraj,
your credit history is scary!

00:58:17.833 --> 00:58:24.041
How can I trust you
with so much money?

00:58:24.458 --> 00:58:27.708
But my family will lose
it’s respect if the shop…

00:58:27.708 --> 00:58:30.500
You Bengalis might
not have anything else…

00:58:31.333 --> 00:58:35.833
…but you care a lot about
respect and prestige. Don’t you?

00:58:37.125 --> 00:58:41.041
Abhiraj, I’m a businessman.

00:58:42.166 --> 00:58:45.958
I’m offering an
open deal to you.

00:58:47.291 --> 00:58:49.750
Deliver the object.

00:58:50.791 --> 00:58:54.166
And take your money.

00:58:55.458 --> 00:58:59.208
It won’t be a loan.
Consider it an income.

00:59:00.291 --> 00:59:01.833
You don’t get it.

00:59:02.916 --> 00:59:04.666
-There’s too much sentiment…

00:59:04.666 --> 00:59:05.583
-Then let it be.

00:59:06.708 --> 00:59:08.750
Live the rest of your
