has no aristrocracy.

01:19:18.458 --> 01:19:19.583
He’s a country mouse.

01:19:20.541 --> 01:19:23.125
-You look like you drink.

01:19:23.166 --> 01:19:23.958
-No, I don’t.

01:19:23.958 --> 01:19:25.541
Oh my God! That’s strange!

01:19:26.625 --> 01:19:27.750
You don’t drink!

01:19:28.250 --> 01:19:29.791
Do you prefer baby food?

01:19:30.083 --> 01:19:32.083
Please give up the liquor,
Chandu.

01:19:32.416 --> 01:19:34.125
And save your liver.

01:19:35.416 --> 01:19:37.583
What are you saying?

01:19:37.750 --> 01:19:40.750
Everything is
going to rot anyway.

01:19:41.083 --> 01:19:44.125
This is the way of the world.

01:19:44.458 --> 01:19:46.833
Do6n’t worry. Just dri6nk.

01:19:47.125 --> 01:19:48.208
And give me 2000 bucks.

01:19:48.208 --> 01:19:50.583
Hey, just get out of here.

01:19:51.333 --> 01:19:53.541
Why are you hitting
my son again?

01:19:54.083 --> 01:19:55.416
He just wanted his medicine.

01:19:55.750 --> 01:19:56.750
I’ll tell you what to do.

01:19:57.333 --> 01:20:00.666
Give him some folidol
first thing in the morning.

01:20:01.083 --> 01:20:04.500
-What should I give him?
-Folidol.

01:20:05.375 --> 01:20:07.083
No one understands my pain.

01:20:07.375 --> 01:20:08.166
-Why don’t you
take some folidol too.

01:20:08.416 --> 01:20:09.583
Why are you still
standing there?

01:20:09.750 --> 01:20:10.791
Get out of here.

01:20:10.958 --> 01:20:15.875
No Mom… This is disgusting!

01:20:17.291 --> 01:20:18.375
Sakhhi Gopal.

01:20:22.708 --> 01:20:24.041
-Did he want money? -Yes.

01:20:24.583 --> 01:20:27.875
My son is a spoilt brat.

01:20:30.125 --> 01:20:34.375
Not everyone is
fortunate like Somnath.

01:20:47.333 --> 01:20:48.041
Time’s up.

01:20:49.625 --> 01:20:52.208
What are the offerings
in the Laxmi festival?

01:20:54.041 --> 01:20:56.625
-Fruits,sweets…

01:20:56.708 --> 01:20:58.500
-Apart from that?

01:21:00.375 --> 01:21:03.041
Sweet coco6nut fritters…

01:21:04.083 --> 01:21:06.750
Nope, it’s something else.

01:22:33.041 --> 01:22:35.333
-Here you go… -That’s enough…

01:22:36.958 --> 01:22:42.625
The fragrance of the Gobindobhog
rice is just so special… Isn’t it Asutosh?

01:22:43.125 --> 01:22:48.000
Feed him properly… Don’t be shy.

01:22:49.250 --> 01:22:53.291
This Goddess Laxmi’s
blessing… Please eat.

01:22:53.541 --> 01:22:57.958
Here you go… Have
you seen Chandu?

01:22:58.416 --> 01:23:00.333
Who knows?

01:23:02.375 --> 01:23:04.500
Why aren’t you eating?

01:23:11.458 --> 01:23:14.250
You’ve figured out the
first part of puzzle, right ?

01:23:14.250 --> 01:23:14.916
Yes! Yes! Yes!

01:23:15.791 --> 01:23:17.250
You’re not going anywhere
till you finish your food.

01:23:17.375 --> 01:23:18.458
Shut up and sit.

01:23:24.083 --> 01:23:25.375
Sit down and eat.

01:23:27.083 --> 01:23:28.958
What’s wrong? Feeling unwell?

01:23:28.958 --> 01:23:32.291
I’ve got it! Eat slowly.

01:23:36.000 --> 01:23:37.833
Why have you brought
me to Lal Bazaar?

01:23:39.958 --> 01:23:40.583
Come…

01:23:41.333 --> 01:23:42.333
Please tell me.

01:23:43.166 --> 01:23:46.125
Lal Bazar’s Lal Mohan Seth was
one of the oldest residents of Kolkata.

01:23:46.625 --> 01:23:50.625
The rice offering to their deity
Gobindo was grown right here.

01:23:50.750 --> 01:23:53.541
-And that rice is called Gobindobhog. Right!
-Gobindobhog.

01:23:53.708 --> 01:23:55.166
And what about the
reflection on the lake ?

01:23:55.458 --> 01:23:57.125
This Old Mission
Church’s reflection…

01:23:57.125 --> 01:23:58.208
…would fall on the lake.

01:23:58.333 --> 01:24:01.041
The church was red. That’s
why since the reflection was red…

01:24:01.375 --> 01:24:02.375
It was called Lal
Dighi or Red Lake.

01:24:02.958 --> 01:24:05.291
And the object of thet reflection is this,
the Old Mission Church.

01:24:05.291 --> 01:24:09.125
-And this is where Madhusudan was initiated…
-Oh God!

01:24:09.375 --> 01:24:12.208
Madhusudan Dutt was influenced
by Krishna Mohan Bandopadhyay.

01:24:12.250 --> 01:24:14.916
And he converted to Christianity here
in the Old Mission Church. Now, let’s go.

01:24:16.416 --> 01:24:21.375
The high priest
is then the Father?

01:24:43.125 --> 01:24:45.791
This is a strange coincidence,
My son.

01:24:46.250 --> 01:24:49.375
My name is also Krishna
Mohan Bandopadhyay.

01:24:50.750 --> 01:24:52.833
Somnath met me quite often.

01:24:54.000 --> 01:24:57.125
He had a lot of questions about
the Old churches of Kolkata.

01:24:59.250 --> 01:25:00.333
This is the letter.

01:25:01.125 --> 01:25:02.875
I’m free today.

01:25:05.791 --> 01:25:09.000
You said you’re not
related to Somnath.

01:25:10.666 --> 01:25:11.625
No,we’re not related.

01:25:12.375 --> 01:25:13.333
Strange.

01:25:15.625 --> 01:25:19.958
The same gait,
the same sharpness…

01:25:20.291 --> 01:25:21.291
Strangely…

01:25:22.375 --> 01:25:25.083
You and Somnath…

01:26:55.708 --> 01:26:57.041
Have you noticed something?

01:26:58.000 --> 01:27:03.791
Everyone who has met Somnath
like the gardener,the Father…

01:27:04.583 --> 01:27:07.083
They were both trying
to tell you something.

01:27:07.750 --> 01:27:09.291
And they are the
ones who got killed.

01:27:12.458 --> 01:27:15.791
No.. Jorashankho’s Nando
kumar didn’t say anything…

01:27:16.333 --> 01:27:18.083
He has also met Somnath.

01:27:21.000 --> 01:27:24.541
Nando Kumar didn’t
say anything to me.

01:27:26.875 --> 01:27:28.666
Because he has
lost his eyesight.

01:27:32.708 --> 01:27:35.375
A storm is brewing.

01:27:39.791 --> 01:27:40.958
Sakhhi Gopal…

01:27:42.708 --> 01:27:43.958
- You know everything,
don’t you ?

01:27:44.291 --> 01:27:45.625
-What do I know?

01:27:51.000 --> 01:27:53.666
Why did you say that to me,
Sakhhi Gopal?

01:27:55.458 --> 01:27:56.666
What did I say?

01:27:58.125 --> 01:27:59.541
When Chandu was
asking for money…

01:28:00.083 --> 01:28:02.750
You’d said you were not as
fortunate as Somnath Das.

01:28:03.916 --> 01:28:04.916
Why did you say that?

01:28:06.583 --> 01:28:13.375
And the day I had moved in,
you said I’m smarter.

01:28:15.208 --> 01:28:17.125
Who am I smarter than,
Sakhhi Gopal?

01:28:19.333 --> 01:28:22.750
-I don’t know what you’re talking about…
-You know everything…

01:28:23.375 --> 01:28:24.583
Please,
don’t keep secrets anymore.

01:28:26.083 --> 01:28:30.500
My gait, my way of talking…
It’s all too familiar. Isn’t it?

01:28:34.291 --> 01:28:35.583
Who am I like, Sakhhi Gopal?

01:28:49.083 --> 01:28:51.750
You… Wait…

01:29:01.666 --> 01:29:06.000
If anyone gets to know… I’ll
be thrown out of this house.

01:30:22.791 --> 01:30:24.083
Doomsday is here, Asutosh!

01:30:25.041 --> 01:30:27.708
Goddess Laxmi's
nose ring is missing

01:30:41.333 --> 01:30:42.208
What happened?

01:30:43.125 --> 01:30:43.875
Where were you?

01:30:44.958 --> 01:30:47.875
-I should have told you…
-What’s wrong?

01:30:48.833 --> 01:30:50.416
You’ve been misbehaving
since yesterday.

01:30:52.333 --> 01:30:55.000
I’ll explain it to
you in your way.

01:30:55.833 --> 01:30:57.625
What are you talking about?

01:30:58.166 --> 01:30:59.916
-What did I do ?

01:30:59.916 --> 01:31:01.291
- What was the riddle?

01:31:01.916 --> 01:31:05.708
“Thanks to the Briton, Permanent is the arrangement
Kali resides in Shankar’s heart Since times ancient”

01:31:06.333 --> 01:31:11.041
It’s reffering to Lord Cornwallis’
Permanent Settlement.

01:31:12.041 --> 01:31:14.708
This gave rise to a new class of workers,
the official clerks, Under the Zamindari.

01:31:16.041 --> 01:31:20.375
I went to Bidhan Sarani formerly
known as the Cornwalis Street.

01:31:22.250 --> 01:31:23.000
THANTHANIA KALI TEMPLE

01:31:23.000 --> 01:31:23.958
1110/1424

01:31:24.708 --> 01:31:26.250
In 1110,
according to the Bengali calendar,

01:31:26.916 --> 01:31:33.916
Shankar Ghosh built this
Kali Temple and the idol.

01:31:34.875 --> 01:31:42.500
And that’s why,” Kali resides in
Shankar’s heart Since times ancient”…

01:31:43.708 --> 01:31:46.666
The same words can
mean several things.

01:31:46.958 --> 01:31:51.583
It might be Shankar Ghosh
or Lord Shankar or.. Or?

01:31:52.166 --> 01:31:57.250
I’m doing this work with such
enthusiasm as a student of History…

01:31:58.541 --> 01:31:59.750
But I might have
some other end to it.

01:32:00.541 --> 01:32:01.500
Isn’t it Brishti ?

01:32:04.291 --> 01:32:05.541
What’s up with you?

01:32:05.750 --> 01:32:10.625
“Everyday devotees bow down their heads Under
their feet is where the last clue is embedded.”

01:32:12.791 --> 01:32:19.041
“He requested for the job in the cashbook
Bidyasunder fetched him the title of Kaviranjan”

01:32:19.666 --> 01:32:27.333
“Check the Bagbazar Library’s north-east corner
“All the rejected tales will have a merger.”

01:32:28.208 --> 01:32:29.958
One.

01:32:32.750 --> 01:32:35.000
“He requested for
the job in the cashbook

01:32:35.458 --> 01:32:40.416
Ram Prasad Sen was employed as an accountant
In the Mitra household of Bagbazar.

01:32:40.833 --> 01:32:43.083
And in that cashbook,
he wrote his songs.

01:32:43.500 --> 01:32:46.166
“Give me the caretaker’s job I am
a faithful devotee, Goddess Kali.”

01:32:47.375 --> 01:32:50.041
“Bidyasunder fetched
him the title of Kaviranjan”

01:32:51.250 --> 01:32:55.625
He wrote the epic “Bidya Sundar” At the
request of Nadia’s King Krishna Chandra.

01:32:56.458 --> 01:32:58.708
The King was so happy that he
bestowed the “Kaviranjan” title on him.

01:33:00.916 --> 01:33:04.833
Now, you know the riddle
talks about Ram Prasad Sen.

01:33:09.166 --> 01:33:10.416
Where are you going?

01:33:12.208 --> 01:33:13.458
Bagbazar Library…

01:33:14.000 --> 01:33:15.291
That’s where the object…

01:33:17.250 --> 01:33:18.041
I’ve told you this too…

01:33:20.166 --> 01:33:21.708
I’m really stupid, Brishti.

01:34:08.666 --> 01:34:10.083
Where is the prince?

01:34:12.416 --> 01:34:19.041
My little prince,
who did you sell the real thing to ?

01:34:19.541 --> 01:34:22.208
Believe me, I didn’t know.

01:34:22.416 --> 01:34:24.208
I thought this was the original.

01:34:24.208 --> 01:34:25.083
Shut up, you idiot.

01:34:27.833 --> 01:34:29.000
Don’t say another word.

01:34:30.541 --> 01:34:31.375
What is this ?

01:34:31.375 --> 01:34:32.125
What is this ?

01:34:33.583 --> 01:34:35.083
Listen to me carefully, Abhiraj.

01:34:36.166 --> 01:34:37.208
Listen very carefully.

01:34:38.166 --> 01:34:46.541
I’ll destroy you if you don’t
bring me the original nose ring.

01:34:46.916 --> 01:34:52.708
One phone call and the bank
will take possession of your shop.

01:34:53.958 --> 01:34:56.208
Give me a phone.

01:34:57.083 --> 01:35:02.000
I’ll ruin your entire family.

01:35:03.083 --> 01:35:07.666
Who am I? Amirchand Mittal

01:35:08.875 --> 01:35:13.125
okey. Give me some more time.

01:35:18.875 --> 01:35:19.333
Yeah?

01:35:21.250 --> 01:35:25.000
Yes,yes, follow him.

01:35:26.083 --> 01:35:28.541
I’m on my way.

01:35:29.250 --> 01:35:32.958
-Admit it! Admit that you’ve stolen it.
-Please don’t hurt him.

01:35:33.041 --> 01:35:36.916
-You dishonest scum. Admit it.
-Let me go. I haven’t done anything.

01:35:37.125 --> 01:35:41.041
-You’ve stolen the nose ring…
-I haven’t stolen anything…

01:35:41.166 --> 01:35:45.166
-Abhi,Please stop…
-I haven’t stolen anything… Mom!

01:35:45.833 --> 01:35:48.208
-I don’t know anything…
-Tell me…

01:35:48.291 --> 01:35:51.083
Asutosh,
Please ask Abhi to stop.

01:35:51.250 --> 01:35:52.250
I haven’t stolen anything…

01:35:52.250 --> 01:35:56.166
My son is a drunk,
jobless guy. But he’s not a thief.

01:35:56.625 --> 01:35:59.208
Please, ask him to stop,
Asutosh.

01:35:59.333 --> 01:36:04.333
-Soham,what’s the matter.
-Come with me. I’ll explain everything.

01:36:04.500 --> 01:36:09.916
The north-east corner…
Not that side. This way.

01:36:10.708 --> 01:36:12.958
Please ask him to stop.
He’s going to kill my son.

01:36:13.041 --> 01:36:14.750
-One good beating
and you’ll talk…

01:36:14.875 --> 01:36:18.541
-Abhi,
listen… Uncle,please save me.

01:36:18.791 --> 01:36:21.125
I swear I didn’t steal anything.

01:36:21.458 --> 01:36:22.416
Stop lying…
-I have not stolen anything…

01:36:22.416 --> 01:36:23.833
-Please let him go…
-I haven’t done anything…

01:36:23.958 --> 01:36:26.583
-I’m begging you please…
-I’ll finish you off today…

01:36:26.750 --> 01:36:29.791
-No… Please don’t hurt my
father… He doesn’t know anything.

01:36:30.041 --> 01:36:34.041
I stole it and sold it off.

01:36:35.708 --> 01:36:37.291
Mom…

01:36:46.708 --> 01:36:50.333
Mom… Mom…

01:37:01.916 --> 01:37:06.791
Hey, hey, hey… Ram Prasad
Sen’s picture in the north-east corner.

01:37:07.083 --> 01:37:09.666
What are you doing, Soham?

01:37:14.375 --> 01:37:15.833
My goodness!

01:37:17.500 --> 01:37:20.916
I had heard about
it from Harinath.

01:37:21.291 --> 01:37:26.250
He was the librarian before me.
There’s a secret locker in this library.

01:37:26.916 --> 01:37:28.416
And it’s made of a special
gunpowder coating on the inside.

01:37:28.750 --> 01:37:33.250
-If anyone tries to break it…
-It’ll burst.

01:37:34.541 --> 01:37:37.666
Yes but how did you know ?

01:37:39.125 --> 01:37:43.541
I think Harinath and
Somnath Das did it together.

01:37:44.041 --> 01:37:48.041
Somnath Das… Who is Somnath Das?

01:37:52.916 --> 01:37:56.208
Dad, Chandu is not a thief.

01:37:57.416 --> 01:38:00.333
Why didn’t you stop Abhi when
he was going to hit Sakhhi Gopal?

01:38:00.333 --> 01:38:01.750
You just stood there…

01:38:03.666 --> 01:38:06.541
How can I call my
own son a thief?

01:38:14.750 --> 01:38:16.416
This is the original.

01:38:19.666 --> 01:38:22.375
I knew Abhiraj is going
to do something like this.

01:38:22.541 --> 01:38:25.916
I made an exact replica.

01:38:27.208 --> 01:38:29.208
I replaced it a
couple of days back.

01:38:35.500 --> 01:38:39.416
How can I call my own son
a thief? That too in public…

01:38:39.750 --> 01:38:43.291
That’s why it’s easier
to blame someone else.

01:38:44.916 --> 01:38:49.458
Throws one off the track…

01:38:50.666 --> 01:38:54.416
Especially in an
aristocatic family.

01:38:55.416 --> 01:38:58.291
We’re not going to live in
house after all the persecution.

01:38:58.833 --> 01:38:59.791
We’ll leave here.

01:39:00.208 --> 01:39:04.166
But before I leave
I’ll spill all the beans.

01:39:13.916 --> 01:39:15.291
The letters…

01:39:17.291 --> 01:39:23.500
Thanthania, one… 1

01:39:23.833 --> 01:39:26.041
Nine, five, six, four, one.

01:39:26.250 --> 01:39:31.750
Five,six,four,one.

01:40:00.541 --> 01:40:04.000
“The last remains of
Alinagar’s founder here lies

01:40:04.166 --> 01:40:07.041
Count the number
of grave lengthwise

01:40:07.333 --> 01:40:09.750
Now it’s time to cross the river

01:40:10.333 --> 01:40:13.208
You’ll reach the town’s north-east corner Covered
